From: Claude AI Assistant
Date: Mon Nov 11 2025
Subject: Disable -dynamic-too to avoid race conditions in parallel builds

The -dynamic-too flag causes GHC to build both static (.o) and dynamic
(.dyn_o) object files in a single invocation. This has known race conditions
when building with -jN where one module tries to import a .dyn_hi file before
another parallel job has finished writing it.

Symptoms:
- "withBinaryFile: does not exist (No such file or directory)" for .dyn_hi files
- Intermittent failures that depend on build machine speed and parallelism
- Fails fast on faster machines (aarch64, linux-64), succeeds on slower (ppc64le)

This disables -dynamic-too and forces vanilla and dynamic ways to be built
separately, which is slower but avoids the race condition.

References:
- GHC issue #15969: -dynamic-too has race conditions with -jN
- Affects: GHC 9.8.4 (and earlier versions)

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Ghc.hs b/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Ghc.hs
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Ghc.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Ghc.hs
@@ -76,9 +76,10 @@ compileHs = builder (Ghc CompileHs) ? mconcat
               -- input hash to avoid superfluous recompilation, avoiding
               -- #18672.
               arg "-fdiagnostics-color=never"
-            , (hasVanilla && hasDynamic) ? builder (Ghc CompileHs) ?
-              platformSupportsSharedLibs ? way vanilla ?
-              arg "-dynamic-too"
+            -- Disable -dynamic-too to avoid race conditions (GHC #15969)
+            -- Build vanilla and dynamic separately instead
+            -- , (hasVanilla && hasDynamic) ? builder (Ghc CompileHs) ?
+            --   platformSupportsSharedLibs ? way vanilla ?
+            --   arg "-dynamic-too"
             , commonGhcArgs
             , ghcLinkArgs
             , defaultGhcWarningsArgs
